\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENNReal/Basic.html#ENNReal\">ENNReal</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `s` is measurable then `preVariationFun f s` is the supremum over partitions `P` of `s` of\nthe quantity `∑ p ∈ P.parts, f p`. If `s` is not measurable then it is set to `0`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/PreVariation.html#MeasureTheory.preVariationFun","kind":"def","line":52,"name":"MeasureTheory.preVariationFun","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/PreVariation.lean#L52-L57"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.Normed.Group.Basic","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.VectorMeasure.Basic","Mathlib.Order.Partition.Finpartition"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Measure.PreVariation"}